      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While I understand your desire to manage this at home, it's important to use your albuterol inhaler exactly as prescribed by your healthcare provider. Overuse can lead to side effects and may not be effective for long-term management. As for supplements, it's best to consult with a healthcare provider before starting any new supplement, especially for respiratory issues. They can provide you with safe and evidence-based options. In the meantime, make sure you keep your inhaler handy, stay hydrated, and avoid known asthma triggers. But please remember, nothing can replace a proper medical evaluation.",
